quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  26,106,"When their brother Noah said to them, "
  26,107,"Indeed, I am to you a trustworthy messenger."
  26,108,"So fear Allāh and obey me."
  27,79,"So rely upon Allāh; indeed, you are upon the clear truth."
  27,80,"Indeed, you will not make the dead hear, nor will you make the deaf hear the call when they have turned their backs retreating."
  27,81,"And you cannot guide the blind away from their error. You will only make hear those who believe in Our verses so they are Muslims [i.e., submitting to Allāh]."
  28,52,"Those to whom We gave the Scripture before it - they{1} are believers in it.",footnotes:1:[i.e., the sincere believers among them.]
  28,53,"And when it is recited to them, they say, "
  28,54,"Those will be given their reward twice for what they patiently endured and [because] they avert evil through good, and from what We have provided them they spend."
  29,19,"Have they not considered how Allāh begins creation and then repeats it? Indeed that, for Allāh, is easy."
  29,20,"Say, [O Muḥammad], "
  29,21,"He punishes whom He wills and has mercy upon whom He wills, and to Him you will be returned."